  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      3,6-bis(1-methyl-4-vinylpyridinium) carbazole diiodide (BMVC) is an inorganic chemical
      compound (Figure1). The uptake of BMVC in cancer cells and normal cells are different.
      Recently, a simple handheld device (Figure1) based on the fluorescence analysis of stained
      cells was established to instantly differentiate cancer cells from normal cells. The
      investigators want to quantitatively measure the fluorescence expression of BMVC in normal
      and cancer cells and explore the usefulness of this staining in head and neck lumps.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
